        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh adds bounded projection coverage for agent tool-result middleware discovery, so one unreadable middleware registry entry cannot abort Codex/OpenClaw middleware discovery before healthy handlers are reached\n- the branch also covers Codex app-server extension factory discovery, channel setup rows, provider discovery fallbacks beside runtime manifest catalogs, loader cache-key metadata, plugin registry alias reads, provider tool schema arrays, configured model catalog API reads, and the recent mainline conflict surfaces\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `7e8e60812772d8d70305644de2f55f07f688ad93`\n- final local proof ran after a clean rebase on `origin/main` at `2b5ddf8f2ae302ecb576a619ca4a392b14dedd82`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 1 file passed, 7 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware.ts src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware-loader.ts src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware.ts src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware-loader.ts src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- branch diff, PR body, and spec scrubbed for the reported plugin name and private local paths: clean\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- Previous refreshed Codex app-server factory proof: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/codex-app-server-extension-factory.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 1 file, 2 tests\n- Previous refreshed shard proof remains relevant for the broader conflict stack: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/loader.runtime-registry.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts src/plugins/channel-plugin-ids.test.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed 2 Vitest shards; 3 unit-fast files / 51 tests and 4 plugin files / 195 tests\n- Previous configured-model proof: `env CI=1 perl -e 'alarm shift; exec @ARGV' 180 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts --reporter=verbose -t \"dedupes configured models without rewriting provider ids\"` passed 2 files, 2 tests, 72 skipped\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -provider blacksmith-testbox -shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`: blocked before remote execution because Blacksmith is not authenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, provider/runtime/channel/plugin registry projections, model/provider install catalog projections, provider discovery projection, web search install catalog projection, model picker provider catalog projection, web search setup provider projection, provider model-picker flow projection, provider setup flow projection, provider runtime hook-ref projection, channel setup selection projection, configured model catalog projection, Codex app-server extension factory discovery, and agent tool-result middleware discovery no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable env vars, unreadable install/provider metadata, unreadable catalog hooks, unreadable setup provider rows, unreadable setup choices, unreadable channel setup rows, unreadable model-picker contribution rows, unreadable configured model API rows, unreadable Codex extension factory entries, or unreadable middleware runtime/handler entries while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, current head `7e8e60812772d8d70305644de2f55f07f688ad93`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: rebased cleanly onto `origin/main` at `2b5ddf8f2ae302ecb576a619ca4a392b14dedd82`, ran the focused agent tool-result middleware Vitest, ran formatting, linting, commit diff check, private-name scrub, autoreview, and attempted the Blacksmith-backed changed gate listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `agent-tool-result-middleware.test.ts` seeds an unreadable `fuzzplugin` middleware entry while proving the healthy `mockplugin` handler remains listed for the requested runtime. The lazy middleware loader now reuses the same bounded registry projection helper. Existing focused coverage still proves the broader stack around provider discovery, channel setup selection, plugin registry projections, provider tool schema normalization, configured model catalog projection, and Codex app-server factory discovery.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed agent tool-result middleware registry entries no longer abort middleware discovery before healthy handlers are reached; runtime-specific handler discovery can continue with readable sibling middleware.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate did not run because the local Blacksmith CLI is unauthenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required). AWS Crabbox broad gate was not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted local slice plus formatter/lint/diff/scrub/autoreview checks.\n",
